/*
 * HISTORY
 */

	This test confirms the functionality of the XmeConfigureObject
	Extensibility function.  You will need to be aware of the changes 
	of the widget between test cases so please look at the widget
	before continuing to the next case.
#)
	The first case checks that a push button widget string is created and 
	displayed.  The string displayed on the window should read
	"Widget".

#)	Make sure that no error messages are printed in 
	the xterm window.
C)
	This test confirms that the positional values may be set properly
	for the child widget.  Make sure that the widget has moved since
	the previous test case.

#)	Make sure that no error messages are printed in 
	the xterm window.

C)
	This test confirms that the width of the border may be updated.  Make
	sure that the border has increased in size.

#)	Make sure that no error messages are printed in 
	the xterm window.
C)
	This test confirms that the overall size of the widget may be 
	updated. (NOTE the border width has been reset)

#)	Make sure that no error messages are printed in 
	the xterm window.
C)
	This test confirms the functionality of the XmeConfigureObject
	Extensibility function on gadgets.  Again, you will need to be
	aware of the changes of the widget between test cases so please
	look at the gadget before continuing to the next case.
#)
	The first case checks that a push button widget string is created and 
	displayed.  The string displayed on the window should read
	"Gadget".

#)	Make sure that no error messages are printed in 
	the xterm window.
C)
	This test confirms that the positional values may be set properly
	for the child gadget.  Make sure that the gadget has moved since
	the previous test case.

#)	Make sure that no error messages are printed in the xterm window.

C)
	This test confirms that the width of the border may be updated.  Make
	sure that the border has increased in size.

#)	Make sure that no error messages are printed in the xterm window.

C)
	This test confirms that the overall size of the gadget may be 
	updated. (NOTE the border width has been reset)

#)	Make sure that no error messages are printed in the xterm window.

C)
	 Press Exit to end the test.  
         Goodbye.
E)
